storyInfo: Upon returning to his hometown, Ansel repeatedly attempts to figure out if he has saved enough lives to prove himself to his uncle, until he realizes that doctors keep moving forward for those who have yet to be saved.

attributes.content: Is this everything, Ansel?
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Messenger

attributes.content: Yes. Reserve Op Team A4 is heading to Iron Fist City on a mission next month, so I don't need to trouble you to bring anything home for me.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I know, but... don't you need to send some letters to your family?
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Messenger

attributes.content: No... I'm alright.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Just take that letter to my friend. Ngala will figure it out for me.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Oh, right, only the big parcel is for him. This small box of antibiotics is for you. It'll be useful if you get bitten by a gloompincer out in the wilderness. Be sure to keep it on you.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Hah, if I run into your family, then I'll really be in trouble.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Messenger

attributes.content: Alright, I'm off then, Ansel. Thanks a lot.
attributes.name: Rhodes Island Messenger

attributes.content: Right, I ought to get back to prepping myself.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Phew...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Melantha, I can't see you from here. There's no way I can lay down covering fire!
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Two small gloompincers approaching from the northeast! Hold back, Cardigan!
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Keep to Ansel's medic support plan!
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Don't worry, I won't let Ansel down!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Sniiiiff... Sniff... I smell it! It's a lure!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Melantha, the beast tamer controlling these gloompincers is definitely to the northeast. Might be hiding in the darkness of that mine entrance!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Roger that. Steward... fall back, leave this to me.
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: Can you take charge of escorting the target with Ansel?
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: Please lie down, ma'am.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Lie down? Are you kidding me? Doctor, take us back to the vehicle!
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Did you not see the bugs and gloompincers? Did you not hear the bombs exploding?
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Please, trust my teammates.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'll be able to support them from this position, and they'll protect us better than the vehicle's sheet metal.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: A-Are you sure?
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Eeek!
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: The gloompincer that got you was venomous. I need you to remain calm and lie down to slow the bloodflow and get you treated. That's how we'll prevent permanent damage to your nervous system.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: But don't worry, I have an antidote with me.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: W-Well...
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Okay. I'll trust you, Doctor.
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Are you sure you've got the right antidote? What if you mistook the type of gloompincer? W-Will you compensate me?
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: I'm sure I didn't mistake anything. I'm very familiar with the beasts of Rim Billiton.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Alright, now please relax...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Wait, D-Doctor, they're coming, over there—
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Ansel, duck!
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: I dealt with the threats, and I've brought another casualty to safety!
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: Very good, just give me a moment!
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Ma'am, your injection is done. You can rest for a while.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Now I need to treat the other injured on your team. Once all the treatment is finished, we'll proceed with the escort according to the mission briefing.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: *Pant* *pant*...
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Thank you...
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Doctor, as anyone ever told you that, at your age, as calm as you are, you're a little... intimidating?
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: No, I'm just very focused on doing what I need to do.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: But you really are impressive. You must've saved a lot of lives.
attributes.name: Panicked Merchant

attributes.content: Well...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Ansel, what's your status?
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: Why'd you turn all gloomy?
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: The nutritional supplements are in the bag. I'll get to your wound straight away.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Sorry, I was just distracted for a moment.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Hah, it just goes to show that your teammates are trustworthy.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: I'm fine, just a scratch.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: But you... have you found some time to recharge a bit?
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: *Sigh*... Ever since you came back to Rim Billiton, you've been working like this, day and night. You're forgetting to take care of yourself.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: Surely you've had several operators coming to pick up those night shifts?
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: I'm just used to the rhythm of night work.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'm just...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'm just thinking, do I deserve the appreciation I get? As a doctor?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Do you think I've saved enough lives?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: The physical results are in, Melantha, nothing to worry about. Everyone's in good shape, no injuries sustained during the mission, and no worsened infections.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'll tell the others in the morning... huh?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Why are you all still awake? Get to bed!
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Especially you, Cardigan. Don't forget we're going to the Originium processing plant tomorrow! We can't have you falling asleep in the meeting again!
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: But we're not done tasting all these weird Rim Billitonian snacks!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Sugar papaya leaf rolls, fried dandelion fowlbeast egg...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Who wants to try this next one? Hibiscus warned us away from it, saying it's bad for your blood sugar. And Ansel says not to eat it, but he's always stocking up on the stuff. Any takers?
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: After that description, who would say no?
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Hah!
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: —Here, Iron Fist City artisanal peppermint candy. Take a piece.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: Thanks...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: It's tough, what you said today, that thought weighing on your mind.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: If I were you, I would definitely hesitate before walking into that house.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: 'If you don't take my place, can I really call you my successor?' That uncle of yours is real tough. Not easy to answer at all.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: —But you can't let it get to you, you still have to take care of yourself.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: Yeah. Even if you prove yourself a great doctor to your uncle, how are the rest of us supposed to buy it when you tell us to take care of ourselves?
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Alright... I'll finish my midnight snack and then get some rest! Really! No more passing out on the stairs!
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Melantha, do you think we can believe Ansel this time?
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Hm... maybe just this once.
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: Alright then, Ansel, we'll go on ahead! Call me if you fall down the stairs, I'll catch you before you hit the bottom!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Does Ansel still think we don't know Cautuses aren't a naturally nocturnal race?
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Alright, nothing wrong with him sneaking in some late night snacks. It'll help him hold up through PT...
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: —Hello, you've reached the Rhodes Island branch office in Iron Fist City, Rim Billiton.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: G'day, I'm looking for...
attributes.name: Passionate Male Voice

attributes.content: Wait a minute, Ansel? You're the one answering the phone, right? I knew it was you as soon as I heard your voice! You're here!
attributes.name: Passionate Male Voice

attributes.content: —Ngala?!
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: How long has it been since I last heard your voice?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I thought you would've sent word by Messenger telling me when you had time.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Hah, I saw your company's number in the Yellow Pages, so I went for a phone booth.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: The one by your house with all the cartoon stickers? Or the one near the refinery that got burned?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Yeah, nah, the roads here have all been redone. Don't worry, I'll show you around in a few days.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: How did you know I'm just about to rush out the door?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: You think I don't know you?
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Aw, hearing you in such good spirits puts my heart at ease. Sounds like that company is treating you right.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: You remember when you were interning two years ago? We couldn't find anything about your company.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Yeah, I was worried too. The Yellow Pages even had the address and number for the grocer downstairs, so I thought maybe the company was a scam.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Ever since you learned that canned spinach doesn't actually make you stronger, you've been slow to trust.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Ugh, let's not talk about that... I was so let down, after all those hopeful years scarfing down spinach.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: You know, when I was a kid, I really wanted to get into some kind of athletics. Football or factory parkour or something.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: How many times did I say it? I wanted to be like you, tall and strong from a young age, putting in all that work for the family without getting tired.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: But all I could manage was running with the boys for a few minutes before I got winded and dizzy and ended up watching from the sidelines.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: If you hadn't suggested giving me a megaphone to do commentary, I would've probably been standing there alone all that time.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: That time we all decided to sneak out at night to hit the slag field and watch our neighborhood team do the tug-of-war with the boys across the way...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: The floodlights on the slag field were glaringly bright. Everybody was cheering, and I had my little notebook, diligently jotting down all the slogans and comments I thought could be cool.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: It all seems ridiculous now, of course.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Hah, sorry, I ended up going into all that on our call here...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Ngala...? Are you still there?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Oh... Uh, yeah. No worries.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Do you... feel sick at all? Any discomfort?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Have you been taking the medicine I sent you? Remember the self-assessment criteria for Oripathy I mentioned a few times before?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: When do you think you might be free? If you can't go to a hospital for a proper exam, I could at least do a basic checkup...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Pfft! Hahaha! Settle down, Ansel.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: How's your own health, by the way? You had, what was it...? Anemia?
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Oh, me? I'm fine, nothing to worry about at all. I may have been diagnosed with an incurable congenital disease, but I'm only exhibiting mild symptoms...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: But, Doctor, that's not how you put it when you found out I had Oripathy.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: You said something like 'current methods can't cure it,' I think?
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Yes, you're right.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I know you want to save more lives with your skills and prove to your uncle that what you're doing is meaningful.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: But didn't you start studying medicine to save yourself?
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Don't let it get to you.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: ...Maybe I am a bit too eager now that I'm back home. I've got this idea that everything I'm doing has to do with my family and friends here.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Sure, just don't worry so much. Do as you always did, focus on what you can actually accomplish, and leave the rest to your chums.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Let's meet up tomorrow night. The usual place. We'll have a late snack.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: I don't know... are you sure?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Sorry, Rhodes Islanders, I'm still finding it hard to see the value in the Oripathy suppressants you're proposing.
attributes.name: Company Representative

attributes.content: And, as you can see, we have new protective equipment for the workers and two new assembly lines. We have no plans to upgrade equipment or increase Oripathy protection measures.
attributes.name: Company Representative

attributes.content: Your proposal is just too expensive. And it comes with too much we don't need.
attributes.name: Company Representative

attributes.content: Please wait, ma'am...!
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: We've been over this a dozen times now, Doctor.
attributes.name: Company Representative

attributes.content: Let's leave it here for today.
attributes.name: Company Representative

attributes.content: She's wrong, Ansel. They don't have reliable channels for the workers to buy their medicine.
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: But... you gave such a detailed and professional explanation. Why couldn't you convince them?
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: It was always going to end like that.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: In Rim Billiton, people tend to trust the experience of their forebears and the word of mouth from their neighbors.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Especially when it comes to medicine, things are rough for Rim Billitonians, but the medical sector is pretty underdeveloped here.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: So you get people saying things are less serious than they are, mistakenly telling each other they don't need a doctor...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Everyone wants to solve their minor issues at home. So you get quack miracle cures suddenly becoming popular in this neighborhood or that.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I was prepared for this from the beginning.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: But I still feel... a little disappointed.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Oh, but you were so excited when you heard this company was interested in collaborating.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: You prepared so much. You even tried to work with a third-party logistics provider to reduce costs.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Yes, though I had some selfish motives here...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: A big Rim Billitonian company like this will have tends of thousands of workers. I can't help but think some of the workers who get this Oripathy protection could be my friends and relatives.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I really wanted to prove that becoming a doctor meant something, was worth something, that I could do something for them.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: It's really disappointing.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Don't worry, Ansel... This day is done, but tomorrow is a new day.
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: You can try again, like you always do.
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: Yeah! If you believe you're right, just stick with it until you convince them, right? I kind of thought you'd chase her down and keep going, actually.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Besides, you said it yourself, Ansel, you want to save more lives. You can't call that selfish.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: I just...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Ansel. Can you make sense of Uncle Donnie's report?
attributes.name: Solemn Man

attributes.content: Hm... There are abnormal shadows in his organs, taken together with his lung issues, these imaging tests show...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: In a word, it's Oripathy, right?
attributes.name: Solemn Man

attributes.content: Yes, Uncle.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Is there anything you can do?
attributes.name: Solemn Man

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I told him to quit working in the mines, but...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Not everyone has the same options you do.
attributes.name: Solemn Man

attributes.content: I hope you make the right choice. Choose to do what you need to do.
attributes.name: Solemn Man

attributes.content: Maybe I just know the place too well, so no matter how hard I try, I can't do anything.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Sorry, it's time for me to meet an old high school chum. You all head back to the office.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Huh, it's just like Ngala said, even the old phone booth here got renovated... Hah, is it supposed to be carrot colored now?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: The grocer's little window still has that black oil smudge.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Hm, I wonder if Ngala likes soda? I'll buy him a bottle...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: ...If you need medicine, you'll turn to the black market when you get desperate, right?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'm sorry, please hear me out.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Sir, do you need Oripathy medicine?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Um, well, yes... my partner really needs it.
attributes.name: Infected Worker

attributes.content: He's right over there, but he can't stand...
attributes.name: Infected Worker

attributes.content: Ansel looks and spies a familiar figure.

attributes.text: Hey! Melantha! Cardigan! Are you in?! I'm taking my friend in to the office for a checkup!

attributes.content: Shhh... It's okay, Ansel, it just hurt for a little bit. That worker made a big fuss over nothing.
Don't worry about me, it's not worth your time. We haven't met in ages, and you still have to tell me about all the places you've been.

attributes.text: What happened to the medicine I sent you? Do you know how bad you look right now?
\nYou haven't been Infected for long. Why are you deteriorating so quickly? You're a mine engineer, don't you have protective gear?

attributes.content: Relax, you only go to the doctor for serious stuff, right? I'm fine. It doesn't hurt that bad.
There's a lot of workers out there sicker than me. With wives and kids too... I pass the medicine off to them.

attributes.text: No, Ngala, how many times have I told you, you can't...
\nPain is the body's warning system, not a normal thing you're supposed to bear with. And doctors aren't just for serious illness...

attributes.content: Oh come on, your company's medicine really works, I've heard all sorts of great things about it. Ansel, you really can be proud of what you're doing. I know I am!

attributes.text: \nHow is it that I really can't do anything?

attributes.content: Was that man just now... Ansel's friend?
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: He's in bad shape... Under his jacket, he's got lots of exposed Originium crystals on his arms and chest.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: But he's pretty lucid. Meaning it's not an acute infection, he's developed that over time.
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: *sigh*... I think I get why Ansel wanted to be a doctor so badly, and why is family was so reluctant.
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Ansel...
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: ...I've got the test results.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: It's hard to say right to the guy's face. We could help you talk your way out of it, if you want.
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: No need... I already told him.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: He's been mentally prepared for it for a long time. In a mining district like this, Infected keep on working together. I'm sure he's seen... lots of similar cases.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: He's just too used to it all.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: If only I'd come back a bit earlier... if only I'd been harsher when telling him to assess his condition and take his medication...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: If only I had realized that pain perception varies from person to person, if only I could've changed the mindset that doctors are only for serious illness...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: If only medical standards in Rim Billiton were higher, and if only awareness of Oripathy protection measures was more widespread...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: His condition has progressed from mid- to late-stage now. At this point, any suppression methods I know are no longer effective.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: He might have two years, or one... I couldn't put it off any longer.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'm sorry, Ansel... I wish I could help you, or comfort you, but...
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: No, it's alright. I'm the one who's sorry.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I shouldn't have told you all this...
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: ...I'm the sickly one who always needed help, why is it someone else who gets struck down by illness first?
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: Don't pull me, Ansel, I'm worried you could pass out on the street at any moment.
attributes.name: Ngala

attributes.content: Yeah, I'm a better shot with my crossbow now, seeing as I'm stronger and all. Meaning I can support you from a greater distance.
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: I can grasp the tail of those Arts... Don't worry, Ansel, my infection hasn't worsened. I just feel like I'm understanding it better.
attributes.name: Steward

attributes.content: No problem, I'll... move to strike alone. Thanks to Franka's instruction, my swordplay is tougher, and I won't get knocked down so easily.
attributes.name: Melantha

attributes.content: Yes, Ansel. Rhodes Island's Oripathy research is rather advanced.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: But for now, our conclusion is that we can't reverse the progression of the disease. We can only buy some time for our patients, stolen from the hands of death.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Of course, if you aspire to be a surgeon, you may have less direct contact with Oripathy.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: But, since you're a doctor, what we do is more or less the same.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: We look death in the eye and say: 'Not today.' Over and over again.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: ...I... didn't have a choice in the first place.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: I'll never accept that there are things I can't do or lives I can't say.
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: 'Just not today.'
attributes.name: Ansel

attributes.content: That's all I can say... as a doctor.
attributes.name: Ansel
